{"title":"McElveen Goes Ballistic; First to Ride All of Bentonville’s MTB Trails in one Day","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/07/10/mcelveen-rides-bentonville-in-a-day/","date":1625922046000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><p>Earlier this year, Payson McElveen went off, becoming the first rider to cover all 142 miles of Bentonville’s MTB trails in a day. Now he invites all comers to try it (at their own pace), and win a load of free gear in the process.</p><p>On July 6, he released “Trail Town: Bentonville,” a film that recounts the ride, under his Stachehouse Productions label. The documentary focuses on the strategy and preparation that went into the attempt. It also highlights conversations with a few of the “mountain bike capital of the world”‘s notable MTB characters.</p><p><iframe loading=\"lazy\" title=\"YouTube video player\" data-ezsrc=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/rg4awS6ieqo\" width=\"867\" height=\"488\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\" ezoid=\"0.049688666780719926\"></iframe></p><p>McElveen stokes participation and interest by challenging viewers to ride the 142-mile circuit themselves. With help from his sponsors, he leverages an impressive prize pack for two winners.</p><p>The race is on.</p><p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09132441/EOSR7778.jpg\" alt=\"payson mcelveen with riders in bentonville\" width=\"2048\" height=\"1365\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09132441/EOSR7778.jpg 2048w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09132441/EOSR7778-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09132441/EOSR7778-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/0