ikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09132441/EOSR7778-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09132441/EOSR7778-1920x1280.jpg 1920w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09132441/EOSR7778-630x420.jpg 630w\"></p><h3>Inspiration for “The Bentonville Challenge”</h3><p>McElveen took inspiration for his Bentonville excursion from an earlier feat in his hometown.</p><p>“In 2019, I rode all of my home <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2020/08/14/where-to-ride-get-your-rocky-mountain-biking-high-in-purgatory-durango-colorado/\">Durango, CO trails</a> in a day,” he said. “It took a couple attempts, but it was an incredible experience that gave me a totally new understanding of my hometown.” He says the ride made him think about pulling it off in other mountain bike meccas. Eventually, Bentonville stood out.</p><p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09132524/EOSR7926.jpg\" alt=\"payson mcelveen in bentonville\" width=\"2048\" height=\"1365\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09132524/EOSR7926.jpg 2048w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09132524/EOSR7926-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09132524/EOSR7926-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09132524/EOSR7926-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09132524/EOSR7926-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09132524/EOSR7926-1536x1024.jpg 1536w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09132524/EOSR7926-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09132524/EOSR7926-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09132524/EOSR7926-1920x1280.jpg 1920w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09132524/EOSR7926-630x420.jpg 630w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2048px) 100vw, 2048px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb25 src ng ngcb25 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09132524/EOSR7926.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09132524/EOSR7926.jpg 2048w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09132524/EOSR7926-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09132524/EOSR7926-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09132524/EOSR7926-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09132524/EOSR7926-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09132524/EOSR7926-1536x1024.jpg 1536w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09132524/EOSR7926-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09132524/EOSR7926-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09132524/EOSR7926-1920x1280.jpg 1920w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09132524/EOSR7926-630x420.jpg 630w\"></p><p>The film plies McElveen’s personal history and the path that led him to Bentonville. But it also explores the town’s MTB history, as McElveen attempts to emphasize what makes it so special.</p><p>Along the way, he interviews various Bentonville standouts like MTB Hall of Famer Nat Ross, NWA Trailblazers Project Manager Hogan Koesis, and Director of Bike Bentonville Aimee Ross.</p><p>“It’s a massive network of trails,” Ross said. “It’s a labyrinth. So, you put together a maze and the story you’re going to tell doing that… It’s a mad adventure.”</p><p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09132912/EOSR69061.jpg\" alt=\"payson mcelveen riding bentonville\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09132912/EOSR69061.jpg 2000w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09132912/EOSR69061-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09132912/EOSR69061-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09132912/EOSR69061-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09132912/EOSR69061-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09132912/EOSR69061-1536x1024.jpg 1536w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09132912/EOSR69061-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09132912/EOSR69061-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09132912/EOSR69061-1920x1280.jpg 1920w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09132912/EOSR69061-630x420.jpg 630w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb25 src ng ngcb25 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09132912/EOSR69061.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09132912/EOSR69061.jpg 2000w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09132912/EOSR69061-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09132912/EOSR69061-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09132912/EOSR69061-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09132912/EOSR69061-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09132912/EOSR69061-1536x1024.jpg 1536w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09132912/EOSR69061-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09132912/EOSR69061-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09132912/EOSR69061-1920x1280.jpg 1920w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09132912/EOSR69061-630x420.jpg 630w\"></p><h3>The Bentonville Challenge: Open Invitation</h3><p>Through his history of publicized endurance rides and filmmaking, McElveen has gotten motivated to encourage others. Apropos, “Trail Town: Bentonville” concludes with a viewer challenge.</p><p>In partnership with his sponsors (OZ Trails, Red Bull, Orange Seal, Smith Optics, Osprey Packs, and Hammerhead), he challenges riders to repeat the 142-mile ride <span>— albeit over however many days or attempts it takes. A formidable loot awaits two contest winners.</span></p><p>The format is storytelling <span>— whichever two riders share “the most compelling or inspiring stories” will win the prize pack at the end of 2021. The pack includes $1500 in Osprey gear, a 3-year supply of Orange Seal tire sealant, a Smith Trace helmet, Shift MAG eyewear, food from GU Energy, a <a href=\"https://www.avantlink.com/click.php?tt=el&amp;merchant_id=92594cfb-2b30-40ba-ab76-f9c20ed4612c&amp;website_id=3407ca35-0b50-44fe-aeb1-9ab6a93bba54&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.competitivecyclist.com%2Fhammerhead-karoo-2-gps-bike-computer\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Karoo 2 Hammerhead bike computer</a>, and gift cards to local Bentonville restaurants.&nbsp;</span></p><p>Ready for a “mad adventure?” You better be. Learn more about Payson McElveen at his <a href=\"https://www.paysonmcelveen.com/\">website</a>.</p><p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09132458/EOSR7816.jpg\" alt=\"payson mcelveen in bentonville\" width=\"1948\" height=\"1297\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09132458/EOSR7816.jpg 1948w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09132458/EOSR7816-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09132458/EOSR7816-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09132458/EOSR7816-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09132458/EOSR7816-768x511.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09132458/EOSR7816-1536x1023.jpg 1536w,https://bi